The Executive Secretary, Anambra State Health Insurance Agency, Dr Simeon Onyemaehi says about eighty thousand residents of the state have already been enrolled into the scheme. Dr Onyemaechi made this known at Azia in Ihiala Local Government Area of the state on Tuesday, during the enrolment of over two hundred people into the State Insurance Scheme, sponsored by one of the illustrious Sons of the Community. ALSO READ: Incentives for Eastern ports patronage not enough ― Stakeholders Inferno kills secondary school student in Anambra Anambra health commissioner applauds EU, WHO collaboration Anambra commissioner calls for paradigm shift in… Foundation donates 4,300 bags of rice to APC supporters in… Addressing the people of the area, Dr Onyemaechi who said that the Health Insurance Scheme is an initiative of the Obiano administration, noted that so far about eighty thousand citizens of the State have already been enrolled into the scheme. He explained that two hundred and sixty-three health facilities are currently implementing the scheme in the State and urged affluent individuals to register their people into the scheme, as Governor Willie Obiano has committed enough resources into the scheme to make it functional in the state. An indigene of the Community, Professor Dennis Aribodor, who is a lecturer at the Nnamdi Azikiwe University Awka, described the State’s health insurance scheme as a welcome development and thanked their benefactor for his magnanimity. TribuneOnline gathered that with one thousand naira monthly and twelve thousand naira annually, anybody can enrol in the State Health Insurance Agency. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE